            <offset>0</offset>
            <sentence>
                <offset>0</offset>
                <text>A 2- years old boy, offspring of non-consanguineous parents and of a 2nd pregnancy, was referred to the endocrine and metabolic center of the Nemazee Hospital, located in southwestern Iran, for evaluation of short stature.</text>
                <annotation id="1">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004322</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="208"/>
                    <text>short stature</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>223</offset>
                <text>The patient was born at 38 weeks of gestation by cesarean section and was healthy by Apgar scoring.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>323</offset>
                <text>Birth weight was 3100 g, length 45 cm and head circumference 35 cm.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>391</offset>
                <text>He had no dysmorphic features and general physical examination revealed no pathology.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>477</offset>
                <text>There was no satisfactory length gain after birth, as noticed by his parents.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>555</offset>
                <text>At the referral time at age 2 years the patient had a weight of 8200 g (-4 SD), a length of 71 cm [-4 standard deviation (SD)].</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>683</offset>
                <text>Head circumference was 48 cm (0.3 SD).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>722</offset>
                <text>Fingers of the hand were extremely short and broad with small nails; there was no redundant skin on the fingers (Figure 1).</text>
                <annotation id="2">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="7" offset="0"/>
                    <text>Fingers</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="3">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="7" offset="0"/>
                    <text>Fingers</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="4">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="5" offset="35"/>
                    <text>short</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="6">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="5" offset="45"/>
                    <text>broad</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="8">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0001792</infon>
                    <location length="11" offset="56"/>
                    <text>small nails</text>
                </annotation>
                <relation id="5">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.PhenotypeRelations</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0009381</infon>
                    <node refid="2" role="source"/>
